<div class="dhui-guide">

  <section class="dhui-guide-section dhui-guide-section--warning">
    <h2 class="dhui-guide-section__title">
      <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
      Requirement: Linked Actor
    </h2>
    <p class="dhui-guide-section__body">
      To request item identification, <strong>the player character must be linked to a user account</strong>.
      Without a linked actor, the module has no way to associate the request with a persistent character.
    </p>
    <div class="dhui-guide-steps">
      <p class="dhui-guide-steps__label">How to link an actor to a user:</p>
      <ol class="dhui-guide-steps__list">
        <li>Right click the user name in the player list an open User Configuration</li>
        <li>Select an actor the user. The user must have ownership over that actor</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="dhui-guide-section">
    <h2 class="dhui-guide-section__title">
      <i class="fas fa-eye-slash"></i>
      Hiding an Item (Mystify)
    </h2>
    <p class="dhui-guide-section__body">
      Right-click any item in the actor's inventory sheet and select
      <strong>"Mystify Item"</strong>. A dialog will prompt you to set a masked name,
      description, and icon that players will see instead of the real item data.
      Confirm to apply the mask.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dhui-guide-section">
    <h2 class="dhui-guide-section__title">
      <i class="fas fa-eye"></i>
      Revealing an Item (Identify)
    </h2>
    <p class="dhui-guide-section__body">
      To reveal a previously hidden item, right-click it and select
      <strong>"Identify Item"</strong> (instant, GM only) or use the
      <strong>GM Identify App</strong> to run a skill check against a DC.
      Once identified, the real item name, description, and icon are restored for all players.
    </p>
  </section>

  <footer class="dhui-guide-footer">
    <button type="button" class="dhui-guide-btn dhui-guide-btn--close">
      <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Close
    </button>
  </footer>

</div>
